Xeon is still a 32-bit processor, and 32-bit Linux also has
an absolute 4GB ceiling on addressable memory for a single
process -- probably even lower depending on your kernel&#39;s
policies.

I think to make the full 8GB useful to Java on such a machine
you&#39;d have to run 2 or more JVMs.

- Gordon

